WEBVTT

00:07.068 --> 00:10.000
[thunder rumbling]

00:10.068 --> 00:13.000
[dramatic music]

00:13.068 --> 00:16.931
♪ ♪

00:17.000 --> 00:18.862
- I can't tell anything
from this.

00:18.931 --> 00:21.068
[indistinct radio chatter]

00:21.137 --> 00:22.620
Where were you standing?

00:22.689 --> 00:24.655
- I was standing
right over there.

00:24.724 --> 00:26.827
- Any shell casings?
- Looked, didn't find anything

00:26.896 --> 00:29.241
'cause I don't think
he was standing there.

00:29.310 --> 00:34.758
♪ ♪

00:34.827 --> 00:36.241
- Rip.

00:36.310 --> 00:38.275
Get my rifle.

00:38.344 --> 00:45.000
♪ ♪

00:46.000 --> 00:48.793
- Here you go.

00:48.862 --> 00:51.793
- You were standing?
- No, I was kneeling.

00:51.862 --> 00:54.931
♪ ♪

00:55.000 --> 00:57.827
[gun fires]

01:02.275 --> 01:04.827
[gun fires]

01:07.896 --> 01:10.724
- You sure you were here?
- I'm sure, sir.

01:14.137 --> 01:16.068
- Give it to me.

01:17.655 --> 01:20.103
Give it to me.

01:31.241 --> 01:32.689
- Hmm.

01:32.758 --> 01:35.000
Just forgot
you picked this up, sheriff?

01:35.068 --> 01:37.862
- That's evidence.
- Where'd you find it?

01:37.931 --> 01:40.275
This time no bullshit.

01:40.344 --> 01:43.551
- Where he said.

01:43.620 --> 01:46.241
- Right where Rip said.

01:54.724 --> 01:56.965
- Say it's about 15 yards.

01:57.034 --> 01:59.724
Pretty damn close.
- Shit, close enough for me.

02:01.931 --> 02:04.275
- That is self defense,
sheriff.

02:04.344 --> 02:06.620
I have no idea why...

02:06.689 --> 02:08.205
you'd want to go ahead
and disguise that.

02:08.275 --> 02:11.724
- [chuckles]
I forgot I picked it up, okay?

02:11.793 --> 02:14.448
Jesus Christ.
- Gentlemen.

02:14.517 --> 02:16.413
[indistinct radio chatter]

02:16.482 --> 02:19.482
- Look at me.

02:19.551 --> 02:22.689
- What the hell are you up to?
- I ain't up to shit.

02:22.758 --> 02:24.448
Now that shell casing
may get him off the hook

02:24.517 --> 02:26.068
with fish and wildlife
but I just pulled

02:26.137 --> 02:27.758
two dead bodies
out of that canyon

02:27.827 --> 02:29.482
and I ain't taking
your muscle's word

02:29.551 --> 02:31.620
about what happened.

02:31.689 --> 02:34.206
- Heard you got a membership
at the sporting club.

02:34.275 --> 02:36.068
How much that cost you
on a sheriff's salary?

02:36.137 --> 02:39.000
- Yeah, well,
it ain't cheap, John.

02:40.689 --> 02:43.724
- I'm starting a list, Donnie.

02:43.793 --> 02:45.896
You just made your way on it.

02:45.965 --> 02:52.896
♪ ♪

02:56.275 --> 02:58.793
The whole county's
turning on me, Rip.

02:58.862 --> 03:01.206
The whole fucking place.

03:01.275 --> 03:08.275
♪ ♪

03:10.413 --> 03:13.586
[solemn orchestra music]

03:13.655 --> 03:20.586
♪ ♪

03:50.275 --> 03:56.965
♪ ♪

04:22.413 --> 04:24.931
- Ugh.
[vomits]

04:30.344 --> 04:32.206
- Who the fuck are you?

04:32.275 --> 04:33.689
- Oh--I'm--

04:33.758 --> 04:37.172
- Ah, clean your mouth
for crying out loud.

04:37.241 --> 04:38.724
- [gags]

04:38.793 --> 04:40.241
[retching]

04:40.310 --> 04:43.896
- He's my assistant, Daddy.

04:45.310 --> 04:47.758
Drink this.

04:47.827 --> 04:50.689
Walk it off.
I need you focused.

04:53.275 --> 04:56.689
Walk it off is a metaphor,
Jason.

04:56.758 --> 04:59.620
Go inside, take a shower.

05:04.310 --> 05:06.275
- Don't see much focus
in his future.

05:06.344 --> 05:08.241
- [chuckles]
Ah, he'll be fine.

05:08.310 --> 05:10.413
Hangovers build character.

05:10.482 --> 05:13.241
- We need a new attorney
for the ranch.

05:13.310 --> 05:15.413
Why, what did Jamie do?

05:15.482 --> 05:18.206
- Chose himself.

05:18.275 --> 05:19.931
- Well,
that shouldn't surprise you.

05:20.000 --> 05:23.000
What are you gonna do about it?

05:23.068 --> 05:25.068
- I'm gonna take away
the thing he left us for.

05:30.689 --> 05:33.655
[light piano music]

05:33.724 --> 05:36.896
[indistinct chatter]

05:53.206 --> 05:55.827
- He's here.
- Yeah.

05:58.689 --> 06:01.379
- Governor.
- John.

06:02.793 --> 06:04.620
- John.

06:08.379 --> 06:10.931
- So how can we help you, John?

06:11.000 --> 06:13.689
- Well, let me be
real clear about it.

06:13.758 --> 06:16.034
I want Jamie out of the race.

06:16.103 --> 06:18.482
- Well, we're pretty far
down the road on that.

06:18.551 --> 06:20.931
- His campaign has
a lot of energy.

06:21.000 --> 06:22.379
- Things are different, John.

06:22.448 --> 06:24.068
You know, the days
of appointing politicians

06:24.137 --> 06:25.758
are over.
- That's ironic.

06:25.827 --> 06:29.000
I think I appointed
both of you.

06:29.068 --> 06:30.724
- I think the irony lies

06:30.793 --> 06:32.620
in what we're
discussing next, John.

06:32.689 --> 06:35.655
I really wish
it hadn't come to this.

06:35.724 --> 06:39.034
- We need you to step down
as livestock commissioner.

06:39.103 --> 06:41.931
- You violated federal law
when you sent agents

06:42.000 --> 06:44.000
onto the reservation.

06:44.068 --> 06:46.758
That investigation
is forthcoming.

06:46.827 --> 06:50.000
We suspect it to be
the start of many.

06:50.068 --> 06:53.344
We also understand there are
civil suits filed against you.

06:53.413 --> 06:55.724
- We heard that the EPA
is investigating you

06:55.793 --> 06:57.275
for rerouting a river, John.

06:57.344 --> 06:58.620
- Heard from who?

06:58.689 --> 07:00.655
- I can't allow
a public official

07:00.724 --> 07:02.896
under this much scrutiny
to threaten the other offices

07:02.965 --> 07:05.068
in this state.
Mine included.

07:05.137 --> 07:07.172
There's a giant spotlight
on you.

07:07.241 --> 07:09.896
- You stepping down
dims that light for all of us.

07:09.965 --> 07:12.413
- And once you get
these things behind you...

07:12.482 --> 07:14.344
we'll welcome you back.

07:14.413 --> 07:17.551
- You want me
out of the office?

07:20.137 --> 07:23.068
Find someone who can beat me.

07:26.000 --> 07:27.448
- Well, that went well.

07:27.517 --> 07:29.275
- It went the way
I thought it was gonna go.

07:29.344 --> 07:30.551
So...

07:30.620 --> 07:32.827
now we start looking.

07:37.517 --> 07:39.896
- Yeah.
I really miss Boston.

07:39.965 --> 07:40.896
- Ugh, so do I.

07:40.965 --> 07:43.034
[dramatic music]

07:43.103 --> 07:45.206
♪ ♪

07:45.275 --> 07:47.000
- Stop it.

07:47.068 --> 07:49.379
No, don't touch him.
Hey.

07:49.448 --> 07:51.758
Help!
I need help!

07:51.827 --> 07:53.689
Officers!

07:53.758 --> 07:57.103
♪ ♪

07:57.172 --> 07:58.758
- I never would have
let you walk into a room

07:58.827 --> 08:00.827
like that, son.

08:00.896 --> 08:05.137
♪ ♪

08:05.206 --> 08:08.517
You're gonna make
a great politician.

08:08.586 --> 08:10.344
What a waste.

08:10.413 --> 08:12.965
He's not the next generation
of me, Lynelle.

08:13.034 --> 08:15.000
♪ ♪

08:15.068 --> 08:17.310
The only thing
we have in common...

08:17.379 --> 08:20.068
Is our last name.

08:20.137 --> 08:23.793
♪ ♪

08:23.862 --> 08:25.724
[cow moos]

08:32.172 --> 08:35.275
[cow mooing]

08:39.068 --> 08:41.275
[cow mooing]

08:41.344 --> 08:43.068
- How come
you can't rope like that

08:43.136 --> 08:44.758
when we're roping for money?

08:44.827 --> 08:47.034
- Then I'm thinking about
the money not the fun.

08:47.103 --> 08:50.000
- It's not supposed to be fun.
It's fucking practice.

08:50.068 --> 08:51.551
Walker.
Jimmy.

08:51.620 --> 08:53.620
Get your asses in there.

08:53.689 --> 08:55.724
- On a scale of one to ten.

08:55.793 --> 08:57.793
How bad's the luck from
putting your hat on the bed?

08:57.862 --> 09:01.827
- 'Bout as bad as
changing a horse's barn name.

09:01.896 --> 09:03.793
- Hey,
what's this horse's name?

09:03.862 --> 09:06.206
- Jimmy, you've been riding
this god damn horse for a month

09:06.275 --> 09:07.758
and you still don't know
his fucking name?

09:07.827 --> 09:09.344
It's Ray.

09:09.413 --> 09:12.103
- I thought you rode Ray.
- Nah, I ride Owen.

09:12.172 --> 09:14.206
- All right, well that's not
quite the same as changing it.

09:14.275 --> 09:16.758
- Jimmy, I went to prison
for seven years.

09:16.827 --> 09:18.586
I say you're probably
the dumbest motherfucker

09:18.655 --> 09:22.448
I've ever met.
That's really saying something.

09:24.241 --> 09:25.931
[moos]

09:28.344 --> 09:31.068
[mooing]

09:31.137 --> 09:33.413
- I got him.
- Belly up, Jimmy.

09:33.482 --> 09:36.241
- Look out!
- Let go of the fucking rope!

09:36.310 --> 09:38.068
- Let go of the rope!
[moos]

09:38.137 --> 09:40.000
- Ah!

09:47.793 --> 09:50.724
- That's why we take care
of our tack, Jimmy.

09:50.793 --> 09:53.068
- Ugh.
Oh.

09:53.137 --> 09:55.034
I put my hat on the bed.

09:55.103 --> 09:57.862
And I called Owen, Ray.
- Jimmy.

09:57.931 --> 10:00.551
You need to stop listening to
those yahoos in the bunk house.

10:00.620 --> 10:02.689
There ain't
no such thing as luck.

10:02.758 --> 10:04.241
But I sure
believe in stupid

10:04.310 --> 10:06.103
'cause you prove it
every fucking day.

10:06.172 --> 10:07.724
Now get your stuff
and let's go.

10:07.793 --> 10:09.344
- [groans]
- Get up.

10:09.413 --> 10:11.517
- [grunts]

10:11.586 --> 10:14.068
Where's my hat?

10:35.482 --> 10:37.689
- We got people for that, sir.

10:39.344 --> 10:41.206
- Yeah.

10:44.137 --> 10:45.827
I don't mind doing it.

10:45.896 --> 10:49.034
It's a task I can complete
and God knows I have...

10:49.103 --> 10:51.620
precious few of those.

10:54.482 --> 10:56.793
There's a lot to fix here, Rip.

10:56.862 --> 10:59.551
- You talking about subpoenas?

10:59.620 --> 11:02.448
- Those are a smokescreen,
just can't figure out whose...

11:02.517 --> 11:04.482
hiding behind them.

11:04.551 --> 11:06.482
- You want me to look around?

11:06.551 --> 11:08.689
- Yeah.

11:08.758 --> 11:10.689
I want you
to start with Jenkins.

11:14.137 --> 11:17.103
- How much time
do you got left?

11:17.172 --> 11:19.793
- Don't know.

11:22.137 --> 11:23.551
- Well,
what did the doctor say?

11:23.620 --> 11:26.275
- Nah, I'm done with doctors.

11:26.344 --> 11:27.793
- Okay.

11:27.862 --> 11:31.344
Well, I'm sorry
to hear that, sir.

11:34.620 --> 11:36.517
- John.

11:38.517 --> 11:40.931
- I'm sorry, John.

11:41.000 --> 11:47.000
♪ ♪

11:47.068 --> 11:49.310
- Yeah, I'm sorry--
[chuckles]

11:49.379 --> 11:52.206
I'm sorry too.

11:52.275 --> 11:59.275
♪ ♪

12:12.103 --> 12:13.931
- It's at $9.

12:14.000 --> 12:16.931
- Keep going.
Wait for a down tick.

12:17.000 --> 12:18.482
- You.
What's your name?

12:18.551 --> 12:21.206
- Jason.
- Get out, Jason.

12:26.758 --> 12:29.103
- Your firm have attorneys?

12:29.172 --> 12:31.827
- A lot of them.

12:31.896 --> 12:33.965
- I want you to put
the ranch in a trust.

12:39.275 --> 12:41.482
- Who do I list
as beneficiary?

12:41.551 --> 12:43.724
- Who do you think?

12:43.793 --> 12:45.758
You're the executor.

12:47.000 --> 12:48.965
Don't ever sell it.

12:49.034 --> 12:51.620
Don't let Kayce sell it.

12:51.689 --> 12:53.034
Give me your word.

12:54.862 --> 12:57.206
- You have it.

12:58.413 --> 13:05.448
♪ ♪

13:07.448 --> 13:10.241
- Get Jamie off the payroll.

13:10.310 --> 13:17.310
♪ ♪

13:29.068 --> 13:32.068
[phone ringing]

13:37.379 --> 13:39.517
- Oh, I know Grant Cole.
He's a good man.

13:39.586 --> 13:42.931
- We need someone
with relationships in Helena.

13:43.000 --> 13:44.689
- Ah, shit.

13:44.758 --> 13:48.034
- I never thought this day
would come but here it is.

13:48.103 --> 13:49.689
- You're going to rehab.

13:49.758 --> 13:52.137
- [chuckles]

13:52.206 --> 13:55.172
Look at those hips.
Well done, Jamie.

13:55.241 --> 13:57.172
Now all those
strap on fantasies

13:57.241 --> 13:58.931
can come true.

13:59.000 --> 14:00.620
He's all yours.

14:00.689 --> 14:03.551
And when his little
chicken heart let's you down...

14:03.620 --> 14:04.758
You keep him.

14:04.827 --> 14:06.827
- He won't let me down.

14:06.896 --> 14:09.000
- [chuckles]

14:11.965 --> 14:14.034
We're doing
a little restructuring.

14:14.103 --> 14:16.862
You've been replaced
as chief counsel.

14:18.448 --> 14:20.103
- By who?
- By me.

14:20.172 --> 14:21.241
- Pssh.

14:22.482 --> 14:23.793
- You're not an attorney.

14:23.862 --> 14:25.034
- Well,
I have power of attorney.

14:25.103 --> 14:26.586
It's sort of the same thing.

14:26.655 --> 14:28.551
- You can't defend him
in court without a license.

14:28.620 --> 14:30.344
You know you have to pass
the bar to get a license.

14:30.413 --> 14:34.379
- You passed it.
How hard can it be?

14:36.241 --> 14:38.448
I'm gonna need
your credit card,

14:38.517 --> 14:40.172
your bank card,

14:40.241 --> 14:43.000
and the keys to your truck.

14:43.068 --> 14:45.896
- I spent my whole life
fighting for this family

14:45.965 --> 14:47.551
and now I'm just
not a part of it?

14:47.620 --> 14:49.000
- Can't unmake family,
Jamie,

14:49.068 --> 14:51.068
but you can
take their gold card.

14:52.310 --> 14:54.413
You'll be fine.

14:54.482 --> 14:56.275
Bubble butt looks like
she comes from money.

14:58.310 --> 14:59.793
- This...

14:59.862 --> 15:02.620
is the best thing
that's ever happened to you.

15:02.689 --> 15:05.275
- [chuckles]

15:05.344 --> 15:07.793
Come on.

15:10.586 --> 15:13.275
- All right.
[clears throat]

15:13.344 --> 15:14.551
One.

15:16.137 --> 15:17.448
Two.

15:19.137 --> 15:20.517
Car.

15:22.965 --> 15:25.448
- May I?

15:25.517 --> 15:27.034
Wow.

15:28.551 --> 15:30.172
I mean...

15:30.241 --> 15:31.793
[ceramic breaking]

15:31.862 --> 15:33.931
Oops.

15:34.000 --> 15:36.586
Well, I guess I'll just pick up
another one at a yard sale

15:36.655 --> 15:39.827
in a few months for a quarter.

15:51.655 --> 15:53.896
- This doesn't change a thing.

15:53.965 --> 15:56.275
- It changes everything.

15:56.344 --> 15:59.241
- Okay, you have a lot of
feelings running through you.

15:59.310 --> 16:01.793
Let them.
Just let them.

16:04.517 --> 16:06.862
- You wanna know...

16:06.931 --> 16:09.862
how I feel?

16:12.275 --> 16:15.344
[sighs]

16:15.413 --> 16:18.068
I feel free.

16:22.551 --> 16:23.793
["I'd Die Without You"
by P.M. Dawn plays]

16:23.862 --> 16:25.586
- ♪ Is it my turn ♪

16:25.655 --> 16:28.586
♪ To wish
you were lying here? ♪

16:28.655 --> 16:33.517
♪ I tend to dream you
when I'm not sleeping ♪

16:33.586 --> 16:35.344
[harmonizing]

16:35.413 --> 16:39.551
♪ Is it my turn
to fictionalize my world? ♪

16:39.620 --> 16:42.482
♪ Or even imagine
your emotions ♪

16:42.551 --> 16:47.448
♪ Tell myself anything, yeah ♪

16:47.517 --> 16:52.862
♪ Is it my turn
to hold you by your hands? ♪

16:52.931 --> 16:59.482
♪ Tell you I love you
and you not hear me ♪

16:59.551 --> 17:03.793
♪ Is it my turn
to totally understand? ♪

17:03.862 --> 17:06.655
♪ To watch you
walk out of my life ♪

17:06.723 --> 17:09.205
♪ And not do a damn thing ♪

17:09.275 --> 17:10.862
♪ Whoa ♪

17:10.931 --> 17:12.550
- Hey, want something to drink?

17:12.619 --> 17:14.275
- Yeah, water.

17:14.344 --> 17:16.827
- We got a two drink minimum.
- A bottle of water.

17:16.896 --> 17:18.964
♪ ♪

17:19.034 --> 17:23.275
- ♪ Oh, whatever babe,
whatever baby ♪

17:23.344 --> 17:28.103
♪ If I have to take apart
all that I am ♪

17:28.172 --> 17:31.793
♪ Is there anything
that I would not do ♪

17:31.862 --> 17:35.103
♪ Since I'd die without you ♪

17:35.172 --> 17:36.931
♪ ♪

17:37.000 --> 17:40.896
♪ Yeah, baby,
since I'd die without you ♪

17:40.965 --> 17:42.793
Go on.
Leave me alone.

17:42.862 --> 17:46.896
- ♪ Since I'd
die without you ♪

17:46.965 --> 17:52.620
♪ Oh, I apologize
for all the thing I've done ♪

17:52.689 --> 17:57.827
♪ But now I'm underwater
and I'm drowning ♪

17:57.896 --> 17:59.413
♪ Oh ♪

17:59.482 --> 18:03.655
♪ Is it my turn
to be the one to cry? ♪

18:03.724 --> 18:07.000
♪ Isn't it amazing
how some things ♪

18:07.068 --> 18:08.586
♪ Completely turn around? ♪

18:08.655 --> 18:10.689
[harmonizing]

18:10.758 --> 18:13.758
- How would you
like to make $1,000?

18:13.827 --> 18:15.379
- I don't do that anymore.

18:15.448 --> 18:17.310
- No, no, no.
It's not that kind of thing.

18:17.379 --> 18:19.620
I need your help.

18:19.689 --> 18:21.137
- What kind of help?

18:21.206 --> 18:23.827
- Well, the kind that pays.

18:23.896 --> 18:27.137
Look, it ain't dangerous
and it ain't illegal.

18:27.206 --> 18:29.448
- Why can't I have a real job?

18:29.517 --> 18:31.689
- Why does this always have to
be the conversation with you?

18:31.758 --> 18:34.000
- You need help with horses.
You need help with tack.

18:34.068 --> 18:36.034
I can do that.
Hell, I'm doing it right now.

18:36.103 --> 18:37.793
- How are you gonna
help me with horses?

18:37.862 --> 18:39.310
Hmm?

18:39.379 --> 18:41.344
- I break colts.

18:41.413 --> 18:43.000
- Oh, you break colts?

18:43.068 --> 18:46.000
- I bet I could outride
every hand on the Yellowstone.

18:46.068 --> 18:49.000
Ridings on the hips.
You know better hips?

18:49.068 --> 18:51.517
- Avery, I can't have you
in a bunk house

18:51.586 --> 18:53.482
with a bunch of
lonely cow punchers.

18:53.551 --> 18:55.517
It's not a place for a woman.

18:55.586 --> 18:57.758
- Don't worry about me, Rip.

18:57.827 --> 18:59.965
I fight off men for a living.

19:00.034 --> 19:01.413
If one of those cowboys
gets randy,

19:01.482 --> 19:03.724
I'll break his fucking jaw.

19:03.793 --> 19:07.172
♪ ♪

19:07.241 --> 19:08.896
- I'll be back.
- Okay.

19:08.965 --> 19:11.310
- Champagne?
- Yes.

19:22.034 --> 19:25.413
♪ ♪

19:31.758 --> 19:34.379
- Day worker?

19:34.448 --> 19:37.241
- Yeah.
- Tough time of year for that.

19:37.310 --> 19:39.310
Round ups done and...

19:39.379 --> 19:41.137
cabins a ways off.

19:43.379 --> 19:45.379
To help bridge the gap.

19:47.137 --> 19:49.862
- I don't need
your fucking money.

20:00.241 --> 20:03.275
You know what a tie is,
don't you?

20:07.275 --> 20:10.206
It's the leash
your master cut...

20:10.275 --> 20:13.137
'cause he know
you ain't going nowhere.

20:21.275 --> 20:26.206
♪ ♪

20:26.275 --> 20:28.172
- What did that guy
say to you?

20:28.241 --> 20:30.310
♪ ♪

20:30.379 --> 20:32.241
- Nothing.

20:32.310 --> 20:39.172
♪ ♪

20:43.275 --> 20:45.172
[phone ringing]

20:56.172 --> 20:58.103
- Um, what's the matter,
Miss Kendall?

20:58.172 --> 20:59.689
- My last name is Nguyen.

20:59.758 --> 21:03.000
Sarah Nguyen,
you should look it up.

21:13.586 --> 21:15.965
Here's what I've learned
in the last few weeks.

21:16.034 --> 21:20.000
You're a good man.
Your father is not.

21:20.068 --> 21:22.517
Soon the entire country
will know what I know.

21:22.586 --> 21:25.241
The question
I have to ask you is...

21:25.310 --> 21:29.137
do you want to be a subject
of this article or a source?

21:29.206 --> 21:31.034
- That sounds like blackmail.

21:31.103 --> 21:33.620
- Blackmail requires me asking
you for something in return.

21:33.689 --> 21:36.344
I'm just asking for the truth.

21:36.413 --> 21:38.827
Which is an elusive thing
out west, I'm learning.

21:40.862 --> 21:42.931
- Can I talk to you alone?

21:43.000 --> 21:45.206
- Uh, yeah.
Give us a second.

21:50.000 --> 21:52.206
- I fucking knew it.

21:54.758 --> 21:56.413
I need to know everything
your father's done

21:56.482 --> 21:59.896
and everything
you've helped him do.

21:59.965 --> 22:01.827
- He's no saint
but does he bend the law?

22:01.896 --> 22:03.448
Yes, he bends the law.
- I'm not talking...

22:03.517 --> 22:05.620
about bending it.

22:05.689 --> 22:08.551
What is she going to find
when she starts digging?

22:11.448 --> 22:14.103
- Depends on
how deep she digs.

22:14.172 --> 22:16.689
- That is the end
of your career in there...

22:16.758 --> 22:19.793
if we don't
play this perfectly.

22:30.344 --> 22:31.931
What are you proposing?

22:32.000 --> 22:33.758
- We do a story
that focuses on Jamie

22:33.827 --> 22:36.137
as a new kind of politician.

22:36.206 --> 22:38.448
The kind that
seeks out corruption.

22:38.517 --> 22:41.448
And there's no greater source
of corruption than your father.

22:43.172 --> 22:45.551
- New Montana
versus old Montana?

22:45.620 --> 22:49.068
That the focus of the piece?
- Something like that.

22:49.137 --> 22:52.241
I think you'll be
a good attorney general, Jamie.

22:52.310 --> 22:54.034
And I don't think
you can win this without me.

22:54.103 --> 22:57.448
- He's running unopposed.
- Really?

22:57.517 --> 22:58.931
- What happened to your face?

22:59.000 --> 23:01.241
- Car wreck.
- Fell down.

23:02.724 --> 23:04.448
- Yeah.

23:04.517 --> 23:06.482
You're not running unopposed.

23:06.551 --> 23:08.827
You can't win without me.

23:08.896 --> 23:11.551
I don't think
your father will let you.

23:15.275 --> 23:18.413
[indistinct chatter]

23:21.965 --> 23:25.103
- So we're committing
to 400 rooms in the hotel?

23:25.172 --> 23:26.620
- Yeah.

23:28.137 --> 23:30.793
- I'd like to survey
the build site from the air

23:30.862 --> 23:33.068
as soon as possible.

23:33.137 --> 23:34.689
- I'll arrange a plane.

23:34.758 --> 23:36.517
- I see good things
in our future, Dan.

23:36.586 --> 23:38.413
♪ ♪

23:38.482 --> 23:40.517
With us working together...

23:40.586 --> 23:43.965
John Dutton
doesn't stand a chance.

23:44.034 --> 23:45.482
- Well, wait
till you see the blueprints

23:45.551 --> 23:48.827
for the castle I'll build.

23:48.896 --> 23:51.448
Right where
his fucking house is.

23:51.517 --> 23:54.827
♪ ♪

23:54.896 --> 23:57.689
- This one here
from wildlife defense...

23:57.758 --> 23:59.275
is gonna require
a litigator

23:59.344 --> 24:02.482
who specializes
in environmental law.

24:02.551 --> 24:04.689
- We need to find an attorney
who does everything.

24:04.758 --> 24:07.344
- They don't exist, Dad.

24:07.413 --> 24:09.206
One thing
I'll say about Jamie...

24:09.275 --> 24:13.448
his melon head comes
with a lot of information.

24:15.931 --> 24:17.620
Hey.

24:17.689 --> 24:20.551
Can it wait?
- No, it can't wait.

24:20.620 --> 24:22.137
Sir.

24:22.206 --> 24:24.689
- Give us a minute, Beth.

24:29.620 --> 24:31.931
- You ought to listen to this.

24:32.000 --> 24:33.724
They're building
a casino...

24:33.793 --> 24:35.413
With a 400 room hotel

24:35.482 --> 24:37.275
with a housing development
around it.

24:37.344 --> 24:39.827
Right up against your fence.

24:49.103 --> 24:52.482
- Rainwater and Jenkins
are working together?

24:52.551 --> 24:55.241
When I'm gone,
they will gobble this place up.

24:55.310 --> 24:57.965
Rainwater will annex that land
into the reservation.

24:58.034 --> 25:01.620
I don't have a child
who could fight for this.

25:01.689 --> 25:05.241
I'm running out of time, Rip,
and they aren't ready.

25:05.310 --> 25:07.689
My children aren't ready
to protect this place.

25:11.068 --> 25:12.793
- What do you want me to do?

25:12.862 --> 25:15.862
- These problems have to
go away before I do.

25:19.137 --> 25:22.275
- Well, how far away
do you want them to go?

25:22.344 --> 25:24.896
- When they go away
they never come back.

25:24.965 --> 25:28.310
Ever.

25:34.965 --> 25:37.310
- What was that about?

25:42.000 --> 25:44.620
Hey.

25:44.689 --> 25:47.241
Hey, what was that about?

25:47.310 --> 25:49.931
- It's not my place
to tell you.

25:50.000 --> 25:52.137
- I can't help him
if I don't know.

25:52.206 --> 25:53.896
- You can't help him with this.

25:53.965 --> 25:56.413
- I'm trying to get a handle
on all these messes.

25:56.482 --> 25:58.413
Okay, so just don't
do anything reckless.

25:58.482 --> 25:59.965
- That's good advice.
Maybe you ought to

26:00.034 --> 26:02.827
take it yourself.

26:02.896 --> 26:06.379
- Men are such
fucking children.

26:06.448 --> 26:08.724
I thought I made it clear.

26:08.793 --> 26:10.724
This...

26:10.793 --> 26:12.655
it was never exclusive.

26:12.724 --> 26:14.517
- Mm.

26:14.586 --> 26:17.068
Beth,
I don't care who you fuck.

26:17.137 --> 26:18.655
I care about you.

26:18.724 --> 26:20.482
♪ ♪

26:20.551 --> 26:22.965
And I thought we knew
each other better than that.

26:23.034 --> 26:26.448
♪ ♪

26:30.517 --> 26:32.482
[coyote howls]

26:34.517 --> 26:36.586
- If you have three tens
we're fist fighting.

26:36.655 --> 26:39.103
- Actually I do.
- [chuckles]

26:39.172 --> 26:41.586
- Yes, yes.
- We all know I do.

26:41.655 --> 26:42.965
- Here's the river.

26:43.034 --> 26:44.137
Oh.

26:44.206 --> 26:45.827
- Did you get it?

26:45.896 --> 26:47.413
- Is that
your poker face, Jimmy?

26:47.482 --> 26:49.000
'Cause you look like
you got to take a shit.

26:49.068 --> 26:50.551
- I don't think
your bad luck's run out yet.

26:50.620 --> 26:52.586
I'm all in.

26:52.655 --> 26:54.758
- Ooh, I think you're bluffing
but I'm too broke

26:54.827 --> 26:56.689
to take that chance.

26:56.758 --> 26:58.482
- This ain't Go Fish, Jimmy.

26:58.551 --> 27:00.586
I'm all in too.
- Ooh.

27:00.655 --> 27:02.689
- Turn them over, boys.
- What do we got?

27:02.758 --> 27:05.517
- Flush.
- [chuckles]

27:05.586 --> 27:07.310
[all laugh]

27:07.379 --> 27:10.172
- Looks like the bad luck's
done with you, Jimmy.

27:10.241 --> 27:12.310
- Hey, boys.

27:12.379 --> 27:15.551
This here is Avery.
She's the new groomer.

27:15.620 --> 27:17.793
You treat her like a cowboy.

27:17.862 --> 27:19.827
You understand what I mean?

27:19.896 --> 27:23.206
[country music]

27:23.275 --> 27:30.103
♪ ♪

27:36.206 --> 27:38.413
- Which bunk's free?

27:38.482 --> 27:41.172
- Uh...
back on the left.

27:41.241 --> 27:42.827
- Didn't you used
to be at the--

27:42.896 --> 27:45.103
- Yep.
Where's the pisser?

27:46.896 --> 27:50.000
Shower that way too?
- Unless somebody moved it.

27:50.068 --> 27:57.000
♪ ♪

28:15.586 --> 28:17.275
- Well...

28:17.344 --> 28:19.724
might as well
get this over with.

28:19.793 --> 28:26.793
♪ ♪

28:28.482 --> 28:30.137
I don't know why
you're all so nervous.

28:30.206 --> 28:32.758
I had my ass
in every face in this room.

28:32.827 --> 28:36.724
♪ ♪

28:36.793 --> 28:38.793
For the record...

28:38.862 --> 28:40.931
If I wake up
in the middle of the night

28:41.000 --> 28:44.655
to one of you assholes standing
over me beating your root...

28:44.724 --> 28:46.517
I'll cut it off.

28:46.586 --> 28:52.000
♪ ♪

28:52.068 --> 28:55.068
Give me 15 then deal me in,
would you?

28:55.137 --> 28:57.206
♪ ♪

28:57.275 --> 28:59.448
- God, this is not a test
I was expecting.

28:59.517 --> 29:06.517
♪ ♪

29:06.586 --> 29:08.172
- Where you going?

29:08.241 --> 29:10.517
- I've worked for some
strange outfits in my day.

29:10.586 --> 29:13.103
♪ ♪

29:13.172 --> 29:15.000
This place beats them all.

29:15.068 --> 29:20.517
♪ ♪

29:22.689 --> 29:24.965
[horse neighing]

29:26.724 --> 29:28.344
- Shh.

29:47.862 --> 29:51.448
- There's something evil
about this place.

29:51.517 --> 29:53.724
You feel that?

29:59.551 --> 30:02.344
It's like this land...

30:02.413 --> 30:04.586
it don't want us here.

30:06.344 --> 30:08.586
And here we are.

30:11.068 --> 30:13.482
- I felt that way
my whole life.

30:13.551 --> 30:15.413
[dramatic music]

30:15.482 --> 30:17.413
- Ain't a very good feeling.

30:17.482 --> 30:20.137
♪ ♪

30:20.206 --> 30:22.724
- No.

30:22.793 --> 30:25.137
- I'd like to quit.

30:25.206 --> 30:26.758
They won't let me.

30:26.827 --> 30:28.689
♪ ♪

30:28.758 --> 30:31.103
I don't know how to get away
from this place.

30:31.172 --> 30:36.379
♪ ♪

30:36.448 --> 30:38.482
- Hmm.

30:38.551 --> 30:40.724
♪ ♪

30:40.793 --> 30:43.793
- I hate to tell you this...

30:43.862 --> 30:47.413
but you ain't going nowhere.

30:47.482 --> 30:49.517
- Is that right?

30:49.586 --> 30:55.620
♪ ♪

30:55.689 --> 30:57.931
Where's your fucking brand?

30:58.000 --> 31:02.586
♪ ♪

31:02.655 --> 31:04.931
- Mine's on the inside.

31:05.000 --> 31:07.655
♪ ♪

31:07.724 --> 31:09.689
I'm stuck here too.

31:09.758 --> 31:16.758
♪ ♪

31:29.586 --> 31:32.517
[coyotes howl]

31:32.586 --> 31:39.413
♪ ♪

31:40.931 --> 31:44.413
[indistinct radio chatter]

31:44.482 --> 31:46.620
- Let's go.

31:50.482 --> 31:53.379
Pack of wild dogs, your crew.

31:53.448 --> 31:55.517
- What happened?

31:55.586 --> 31:58.724
- Drifter pulled
a knife on him.

31:58.793 --> 32:02.000
Your boy took it too far.
He took it way too far.

32:02.068 --> 32:04.758
But I ain't pressing charges
against a veteran.

32:04.827 --> 32:07.413
And I don't mind the message
this sends to drifters.

32:07.482 --> 32:09.896
This don't change things
with your wrangler.

32:11.965 --> 32:14.241
- Dan Jenkins is not the future
of this valley, Donnie,

32:14.310 --> 32:16.310
and you know it.

32:16.379 --> 32:18.344
- I wish I could
snap my fingers, John,

32:18.413 --> 32:21.000
and make all these pirates
go away but we can't.

32:21.068 --> 32:22.793
- Yes, we can.

32:22.862 --> 32:26.137
You just don't have the stomach
for it and that's a shame...

32:26.206 --> 32:28.689
'cause I remember
a time when you did.

32:28.758 --> 32:32.275
- Stomach ain't got
nothing to do with it.

32:41.275 --> 32:43.724
- Sit down.

32:59.931 --> 33:02.068
- You win.

33:02.137 --> 33:03.758
- [chuckles]

33:03.827 --> 33:06.034
I'm not trying to win anything,
I'm just...

33:06.103 --> 33:08.379
just trying to preserve.
Just trying--

33:08.448 --> 33:10.689
you know, I'm trying
to leave you something that...

33:10.758 --> 33:14.034
you can leave
your son one day.

33:14.103 --> 33:17.275
It feels like that's
all I ever say, I just can't--

33:17.344 --> 33:19.448
I can't get
any of you to hear it.

33:19.517 --> 33:21.793
- I hear it.

33:23.724 --> 33:26.965
I'd like to come home.

33:27.034 --> 33:29.206
If you'll have me.

33:31.206 --> 33:34.344
- Just give me, um...

33:34.413 --> 33:37.206
just give me a couple days.
I can move into the...

33:37.275 --> 33:38.793
guest house.
You and Monica take my--

33:38.862 --> 33:41.551
- She left me.

33:43.896 --> 33:47.034
Cowboys stay in the bunk house.

33:47.103 --> 33:49.241
- I don't need
another cowboy, Kayce.

33:51.862 --> 33:54.068
- The only thing I got left...

33:54.137 --> 33:56.344
is to make a future for my son.

33:57.724 --> 34:00.482
This is the only thing
I got to give him.

34:02.068 --> 34:04.551
I know what you need.

34:04.620 --> 34:11.482
♪ ♪

34:30.379 --> 34:32.034
[all talking at once]

34:32.103 --> 34:33.447
- All right, all right,
whose turn?

34:33.516 --> 34:35.000
Let's go, let's go.
Whose turn is it?

34:35.068 --> 34:36.516
- Pretty sure
it's your turn like always.

34:36.585 --> 34:38.103
- It's my turn?
All right,

34:38.172 --> 34:39.655
just give me a second.
Give me a second.

34:39.724 --> 34:41.172
Hey, you ride
your own horse, cowboy.

34:41.241 --> 34:43.344
I'll ride mine.
All right, I'm--one, two--

34:43.413 --> 34:46.034
you're bleeding me dry here
and somehow I kind of like it.

34:46.103 --> 34:47.379
- All right, um--
- I'm in.

34:47.447 --> 34:49.034
- Everybody's out.
- Okay, great.

34:49.103 --> 34:50.965
- Oh, God.
- I got the Jackson Five.

34:51.034 --> 34:54.516
- Take that, bitches.
all: Oh!

34:54.585 --> 34:56.103
- [laughs]
- Again?

34:56.172 --> 34:57.827
- She cheated.
She doesn't even have sleeves.

34:57.896 --> 34:59.517
- Get me a beer.
Get me a beer.

34:59.586 --> 35:02.793
- Yeah, grab me one too please.
- Mm-mm-mm-mm.

35:02.862 --> 35:05.655
- Jesus Christ.
- All right, settle down.

35:05.724 --> 35:07.034
- Okay.
- Somebody point me

35:07.103 --> 35:08.551
to an empty bunk.

35:08.620 --> 35:11.068
[country music]

35:11.137 --> 35:13.862
- Top, back left.

35:13.931 --> 35:20.965
♪ ♪

35:24.517 --> 35:26.758
all: Don't put your hat
on the bed.

35:26.827 --> 35:28.517
- I don't believe in that shit.

35:28.586 --> 35:30.379
- Nobody told me
that was an option.

35:30.448 --> 35:32.241
- It's not.

35:32.310 --> 35:34.000
♪ ♪

35:34.068 --> 35:36.103
- All right, come on.
Let's play again.

35:36.172 --> 35:37.896
You, big talker.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

35:37.965 --> 35:40.000
- It's your deal.
Let's deal it.

35:40.068 --> 35:42.103
I could use a small
but tasteful loan.

35:42.172 --> 35:44.448
- Yeah, here.
Just help collect.

35:44.517 --> 35:46.551
♪ ♪

35:46.620 --> 35:48.172
- All right, big talker.

35:48.241 --> 35:51.241
Who would like
to give me a small loan?

35:51.310 --> 35:53.482
- I just did.
Someone just give him $1.

35:54.965 --> 35:56.413
- Easy.

35:57.931 --> 36:00.896
Come on.
There you go.

36:00.965 --> 36:02.379
Okay?
- Yeah.

36:02.448 --> 36:03.931
- Okay.
- Sorry I'm slow.

36:04.000 --> 36:06.413
- That's okay.
Little bitty steps.

36:06.482 --> 36:07.931
- How long are we staying here?

36:08.000 --> 36:10.275
- Till she can
take care of herself.

36:10.344 --> 36:13.000
What else you wanna know?

36:30.586 --> 36:32.413
Okay.
You okay?

36:32.482 --> 36:35.000
- Thanks, Grandpa.
- All right.

36:41.172 --> 36:43.310
[dramatic music]

36:43.379 --> 36:45.482
♪ ♪

36:45.551 --> 36:48.379
Look who's home, momma.

36:48.448 --> 36:55.379
♪ ♪

36:57.586 --> 37:00.103
Let me know when
you want to come inside.

37:00.172 --> 37:03.172
[Tate crying]

37:03.241 --> 37:10.241
♪ ♪

37:22.551 --> 37:25.206
- I'm--I'm ready to go inside.

37:25.275 --> 37:27.172
♪ ♪

37:27.241 --> 37:30.172
I'm ready to go inside now.
- [crying]

37:30.241 --> 37:34.689
- [cries]
Oh, God.

37:34.758 --> 37:37.758
♪ ♪

37:37.827 --> 37:40.241
What have I done?

37:40.310 --> 37:47.034
♪ ♪

38:01.344 --> 38:03.034
- Whenever you're ready.

38:03.103 --> 38:10.103
♪ ♪

38:18.827 --> 38:20.689
- I realized
something last night.

38:20.758 --> 38:23.517
♪ ♪

38:23.586 --> 38:27.862
The only way to protect
my father's legacy...

38:27.931 --> 38:29.965
is to destroy the man.

38:30.034 --> 38:37.000
♪ ♪

38:43.517 --> 38:45.862
I didn't think
it was gonna be this hard.

38:45.931 --> 38:50.310
♪ ♪

38:50.379 --> 38:52.482
- Take your time.

38:52.551 --> 38:55.103
♪ ♪

38:55.172 --> 38:56.689
- [sighs]

38:56.758 --> 38:58.724
[chuckles]

38:58.793 --> 39:05.793
♪ ♪

39:09.379 --> 39:10.655
Okay.

39:12.103 --> 39:13.448
I'm ready.

39:13.517 --> 39:18.206
♪ ♪

39:21.000 --> 39:22.517
- [whistles]

39:22.586 --> 39:25.103
[tense music]

39:25.172 --> 39:32.172
♪ ♪

39:45.551 --> 39:48.655
[whistling]

39:48.724 --> 39:50.310
- [grunts]

39:50.379 --> 39:57.310
♪ ♪

40:06.724 --> 40:09.965
- You guys are fucking idiots.

40:10.034 --> 40:13.482
You'll rot in prison for this
the rest of your fucking lives.

40:13.551 --> 40:16.344
- No, no, no.
It happens all the time.

40:16.413 --> 40:19.344
The lost souls they come out
here into the forest and...

40:19.413 --> 40:21.655
They can't bear
to live another day.

40:21.724 --> 40:23.724
So they decide to end it all.

40:25.344 --> 40:27.586
It's really toughest
on the kids, you know?

40:27.655 --> 40:29.793
They never understand why.

40:29.862 --> 40:31.241
- Fuck you.

40:31.310 --> 40:32.896
- Don't you look at me
you piece of shit.

40:32.965 --> 40:34.482
You look at him.

40:34.551 --> 40:37.344
He has to understand
what he's up against.

40:38.724 --> 40:42.000
That semi that ran into
Mr. Dutton's truck...

40:43.689 --> 40:46.517
Was that an accident?

40:46.586 --> 40:49.965
- It was
a convenient opportunity.

40:50.034 --> 40:52.896
- Well, it ain't so
fucking convenient now, is it?

40:52.965 --> 40:54.310
- [grunts]

40:54.379 --> 40:57.172
- I want you to tell him
about the land.

40:57.241 --> 41:00.344
Tell him how you get it.
Go on.

41:00.413 --> 41:03.172
- We'll inflate
the land prices.

41:03.241 --> 41:05.862
Run up the property tax.

41:05.931 --> 41:08.586
And price people out.

41:08.655 --> 41:11.896
You know how much
the Yellowstone is worth?

41:11.965 --> 41:13.413
You think I'm gonna be
the last person

41:13.482 --> 41:15.413
who's gonna wanna take it?

41:15.482 --> 41:18.413
Now your father,
he has two choices.

41:18.482 --> 41:20.206
Either to sell it...

41:20.275 --> 41:23.103
Or to lose it.

41:23.172 --> 41:26.517
And that's the fucking truth.

41:26.586 --> 41:29.758
- Now you know, Kayce.

41:29.827 --> 41:32.172
Jimmy, go on and cut him down.

41:32.241 --> 41:35.724
- Fuck you guys.
Fuck you.

41:35.793 --> 41:37.551
Fucking idiots.

41:37.620 --> 41:39.551
- Yah!
[horse neighs]

41:39.620 --> 41:42.655
- [grunting]

41:42.724 --> 41:49.000
♪ ♪

41:49.068 --> 41:51.172
- Let him hang.

41:51.241 --> 41:53.206
- [grunts]

41:53.275 --> 42:00.000
♪ ♪

42:12.620 --> 42:14.448
- [breathes shakily]

42:23.862 --> 42:26.275
You should buy
a smaller table, Dad.

42:26.344 --> 42:31.137
♪ ♪

42:31.206 --> 42:33.172
- I remember a time when...

42:33.241 --> 42:35.103
♪ ♪

42:35.172 --> 42:38.068
Every seat at this table
was filled.

42:38.137 --> 42:39.931
- No, you don't, Dad.

42:40.000 --> 42:42.827
♪ ♪

42:42.896 --> 42:45.724
That's not a memory.

42:45.793 --> 42:47.827
That's a dream.

42:47.896 --> 42:54.931
♪ ♪

43:02.034 --> 43:05.034
[footsteps approaching]

43:22.965 --> 43:25.862
I thought you said
Kayce came home?

43:25.931 --> 43:28.482
- He did.

43:28.551 --> 43:30.379
- Where is he?

43:30.448 --> 43:32.482
♪ ♪

43:32.551 --> 43:34.206
- He's learning.

43:34.275 --> 43:36.206
♪ ♪

43:36.275 --> 43:38.482
It doesn't matter how many...

43:38.551 --> 43:40.896
people sit
at the table, honey.

43:40.965 --> 43:43.965
What matters is
they have a place to sit.

43:44.034 --> 43:45.689
The table's
the only thing that matters.

43:45.758 --> 43:47.448
I need you to understand that.

43:47.517 --> 43:49.448
♪ ♪

43:49.517 --> 43:52.172
- I'm not doing this
for a table.

43:52.241 --> 43:55.551
♪ ♪

43:55.620 --> 43:59.137
I'm doing this for you.

43:59.206 --> 44:02.206
And when you're gone...

44:02.275 --> 44:04.172
I'll sell the table first.

44:07.620 --> 44:09.517
- Well...

44:11.241 --> 44:13.344
I'm not going anywhere.

44:14.586 --> 44:17.241
- I sure hope not.

44:28.724 --> 44:31.620
["Mercy Now"
by Mary Gauthier plays]

44:31.689 --> 44:37.724
♪ ♪

44:37.793 --> 44:39.793
- [exhales]

44:42.172 --> 44:43.896
- ♪ My father ♪

44:43.965 --> 44:45.586
♪ ♪

44:45.655 --> 44:48.965
♪ Could use
a little mercy now ♪

44:49.034 --> 44:53.517
♪ ♪

44:53.586 --> 44:57.413
♪ The fruits of his labor ♪

44:57.482 --> 45:01.448
♪ Fall and rot
slowly on the ground ♪

45:01.517 --> 45:06.379
♪ ♪

45:06.448 --> 45:09.620
♪ His work is almost over ♪

45:09.689 --> 45:14.172
♪ It won't be long
he won't be around ♪

45:14.241 --> 45:18.793
♪ ♪

45:18.862 --> 45:23.000
♪ I love my father ♪

45:23.068 --> 45:26.758
♪ He could use
some mercy now ♪

45:26.827 --> 45:32.172
♪ ♪

45:32.241 --> 45:37.103
♪ People in power,
they'll do anything ♪

45:37.172 --> 45:39.620
♪ To keep their crown ♪

45:39.689 --> 45:44.793
♪ ♪

45:44.862 --> 45:51.689
♪ I love life and life itself
could use some mercy now ♪

45:51.758 --> 45:59.724
♪ ♪

46:11.034 --> 46:17.689
♪ Every single one of us
could use some mercy now ♪

46:17.758 --> 46:22.413
♪ ♪
